## 1. Module Definition

### Precise Responsibility

The Frontend module is the **sole human interface** for PhysicsCapture. It orchestrates a five-screen workflow, drives the visual sync mechanism, relays commands to backend services, displays streaming progress, and presents final results with uncertainty annotations.

### Explicit Non-Goals

- Does NOT compute any physics or CV outputs
- Does NOT directly invoke ffmpeg or SAM2
- Does NOT persist experiment data (delegates to Node.js)
- Does NOT implement WebRTC STUN/TURN infrastructure
- Does NOT support simultaneous multi-experiment sessions
- Does NOT render 3D trajectory visualisations (Sprint 4 placeholder only in this plan)

### Inputs (typed)

| Name                | Type                        | Units          | Shape         | Constraints                                                   |
| ------------------- | --------------------------- | -------------- | ------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------- |
| `experimentId`      | `string` (UUID v4)          | —              | scalar        | Non-empty, assigned by Node on session creation               |
| `cameraList`        | `CameraDevice[]`            | —              | [0..4]        | Max 4 cameras (1 PC + 3 phones)                               |
| `calibrationResult` | `CalibrationResult \| null` | pixels RMS     | scalar object | null if uncalibrated                                          |
