### 3.3 REST API Contracts

```
POST   /api/experiments              → { experimentId: string }
GET    /api/experiments/:id          → ExperimentMeta
POST   /api/experiments/:id/calibrate  body: {}  → 202 Accepted
POST   /api/experiments/:id/track    body: { seeds: BallSeed[] } → 202 Accepted
POST   /api/experiments/:id/correct  body: CorrectionKeyframe → 202 Accepted
POST   /api/experiments/:id/physics  body: { massConfigs: BallMassConfig[] } → 202 Accepted
GET    /api/calibration/profiles     → CalibrationProfile[]
POST   /api/calibration/profiles     body: { name: string, experimentId: string } → CalibrationProfile
GET    /experiments/:id/frames/cam:c/frame_:n.png  → image/png (static file)

# Video upload (from phone):
POST   /api/upload/:experimentId/:cameraId  multipart/form-data  → { received: true }
```

### 3.4 Time Representation

- All timestamps use **Unix time in milliseconds** (`number`, `float64`).
- The `frameToMs` mapping in `SyncData` uses integer frame indices as keys.
- The Sync Marker maintains a **local, monotonically increasing display-frame counter** starting at 0 on component mount. True timestamps are derived in Python from the recorded Gray-code + grating phase (not from any frontend wall-clock).

### 3.5 Coordinate System

- **Frame coordinates:** origin at top-left of the image frame. X increases rightward, Y increases downward. Units: pixels (float64, sub-pixel precision).
- **Canvas coordinates:** same convention; derived from frame coordinates via the scale transform defined in Section 2.8.
- **World coordinates** (used in results display only): millimetres. X: rightward along ball travel axis; Y: upward. Derived by Python; frontend displays but does not compute.

