### 4.6 Scrubber Synchronisation (Multi-Camera)

When multiple cameras are present, all `FrameScrubber` instances share the same `currentFrame` value from `trackingStore`. Moving one scrubber moves all.

```typescript
// In trackingStore:
setFrame(n: number) {
  state.currentFrame = Math.max(0, Math.min(n, state.frameCount - 1))
}

// Each FrameScrubber:
const currentFrame = useTrackingStore(s => s.currentFrame)
const setFrame = useTrackingStore(s => s.setFrame)
```

Frame counts may differ slightly between cameras (upload timing). The scrubber's max is `Math.min(...perCameraFrameCounts)`.

### 4.7 Hit Testing for Manual Correction

```typescript
function findNearestPoint(
  px: number, // pointer x in frame coords
  py: number, // pointer y in frame coords
  tracks: BallTrack[],
  currentFrame: number,
  maxDistancePx: number = 20,
): { ballId: number; frameIdx: number } | null {
  let best: { ballId: number; frameIdx: number } | null = null;
  let bestDist = maxDistancePx;

  for (const track of tracks) {
    // Search ±2 frames around currentFrame
    for (const point of track.points) {
      if (Math.abs(point.frameIdx - currentFrame) > 2) continue;
      const dx = point.x - px;
      const dy = point.y - py;
      const dist = Math.sqrt(dx * dx + dy * dy);
      if (dist < bestDist) {
        bestDist = dist;
        best = { ballId: track.ballId, frameIdx: point.frameIdx };
      }
    }
  }
  return best;
}
```

### 4.8 Velocity Chart Rendering

```typescript
// Transform PhysicsResult to Recharts data format:
