## 5. Execution Model

| Component             | Invocation                   | Trigger                                     | Concurrency                               |
| --------------------- | ---------------------------- | ------------------------------------------- | ----------------------------------------- |
| Router & Shell        | Continuous                   | App load                                    | Single-threaded (React render loop)       |
| WebSocket Client      | Async, event-driven          | App load; reconnect on close                | Single connection; message queue          |
| WebRTC Peer Manager   | Async, event-driven          | `phone:joined` WS message                   | One `RTCPeerConnection` per phone (max 3) |
| Sync Marker           | rAF loop                     | Screen 3 mount                              | Single rAF callback; no workers           |
| FrameScrubber preload | Async, demand-driven         | `currentFrame` change                       | Concurrent image loads (browser-native)   |
| TrajectoryCanvas      | Synchronous                  | `currentFrame` change; `BallTrack[]` update | Single rAF or direct call                 |
| BallSeedPicker        | Synchronous                  | User mouse/touch events                     | —                                         |
| MediaRecorder (phone) | Async, command-driven        | `record:start` WS message                   | Single recorder per phone page            |
| Upload XHR (phone)    | Async                        | `recorder.onstop`                           | Single XHR with progress                  |
| Export functions      | Async (PDF), Sync (CSV/JSON) | User click                                  | —                                         |

**Timing model:**

- Sync Marker: must complete `tick()` within one rAF interval (< 16ms). Drawing border + 10 squares + low-frequency grating is well within budget.
- Trajectory rendering: O(N_balls × N_frames) per draw call. At 3 balls × 900 frames (30s @ 30fps) = 2700 `lineTo` calls per canvas → < 2ms in Chrome on modern hardware.
- FrameScrubber preload: images are 1080p PNGs served from localhost. Decode ~10ms each. Preload window of 20 frames → ~200ms total, distributed asynchronously.

