## 6. State & Data Flow

### End-to-End Flow

```
Screen 1 (Setup):
  User → POST /api/experiments → experimentId → sessionStore
  Phone → WS join → WebRTC offer → PC answer → MediaStream → sessionStore.cameras
  User inputs masses → sessionStore.ballConfigs

Screen 2 (Calibration):
  User → "Run Calibration" → POST /api/calibrate → 202
  WS stream: calibration:progress → calibrationStore.status
  WS: calibration:complete → calibrationStore.result, .reprojectionError

Screen 3 (Recording):
  Mount → SyncMarker starts, display_frame = 0
  User → "Record" → WS: record:start → phones start MediaRecorder
  User → "Stop" → WS: record:stop → phones stop MediaRecorder → upload
  WS: upload:progress → per-camera progress bars in UI
  WS: frames:ready → trackingStore.frameCount updated per camera

Screen 4 (Tracking):
  Load frame 0 → BallSeedPicker rendered
  User places seeds → trackingStore.seeds
  "Track" → POST /api/track → WS stream: tracking:update → trackingStore.tracks
  User drags correction → POST /api/correct → re-tracking stream → trackingStore updated
  "Compute Physics" → POST /api/physics → WS: physics:result → resultsStore.physicsResult

Screen 5 (Results):
  Read resultsStore.physicsResult → render all charts and tables
  Export → Blob → download
```

### Retained State

| Store                      | Persisted?               | How                                                              |
| -------------------------- | ------------------------ | ---------------------------------------------------------------- |
| sessionStore               | Session only (in-memory) | Lost on page refresh; must restart experiment                    |
| calibrationStore.profiles  | Yes                      | Fetched from Node SQLite on Screen 2 mount                       |
| trackingStore.tracks       | Session only             | Re-fetched from Node if page reloaded (GET /api/experiments/:id) |
| resultsStore.physicsResult | Session only             | Re-fetched if needed                                             |

**No localStorage or sessionStorage is used.** All state that must survive a refresh lives in the Node.js backend.

### Intermediate Representations

- `chunks: Blob[]` — `MediaRecorder` data chunks, held in phone's RAM until upload. Typical size: 100 Mbps × 60s = ~750 MB worst case. Acceptable on modern phones.
- `preloadCache: Map<number, HTMLImageElement>` — FrameScrubber cache. Max 50 entries × ~500KB/frame (1080p PNG) ≈ 25 MB. Acceptable.
- `pendingWSMessages: OutboundMessage[]` — queue when disconnected. Max 20.

