## 13. Observability

### Logging

All frontend logs use a structured `log()` function:

```typescript
function log(
  level: "debug" | "info" | "warn" | "error",
  component: string,
  msg: string,
  data?: object,
) {
  if (level === "debug" && !import.meta.env.DEV) return;
  console[level](`[${component}] ${msg}`, data ?? "");
}
```

| Component        | Event                | Level | Fields                                               |
| ---------------- | -------------------- | ----- | ---------------------------------------------------- |
| wsClient         | connect              | info  | `url`                                                |
| wsClient         | disconnect           | warn  | `code`, `reason`, `attempt`                          |
| wsClient         | message received     | debug | `type`, `size_bytes`                                 |
| wsClient         | parse error          | error | `raw_text`                                           |
| webrtc           | peer connected       | info  | `peerId`                                             |
| webrtc           | ICE failed           | warn  | `peerId`, `state`                                    |
| SyncMarker       | started              | info  | `roi_px`, `bits`, `cycles`                           |
| SyncMarker       | jitter warning       | warn  | `jitter_ms`                                          |
| SyncMarker       | tab hidden           | warn  | `display_frame`                                      |
| MediaRecorder    | start                | info  | `mimeType`, `bitrate`                                |
| MediaRecorder    | stop                 | info  | `chunk_count`, `total_bytes`                         |
| Upload           | progress             | debug | `percent`                                            |
| Upload           | complete             | info  | `duration_ms`, `bytes`                               |
| TrajectoryCanvas | correction           | info  | `ballId`, `frameIdx`, `dx`, `dy`                     |

